in the future: how the palaeorecord can improve estimates of global warming</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Progress in Physical Geography</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/45e39a0a2ca997212fee6634c32644e5"><gtr:id>45e39a0a2ca997212fee6634c32644e5</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Edwards T</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2016-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:outcomeId>doi_53d079079a8156dc</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>4D3EE8A4-DAD0-43B1-A9C1-C8CC130E695D</gtr:id><gtr:title>Evaluation of climate models using palaeoclimatic data</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Nature Climate Change</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/f91ca30f76297e2adb9ec994c2a7bf55"><gtr:id>f91ca30f76297e2adb9ec994c2a7bf55</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Braconnot P</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2012-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:outcomeId>5463ec5b66ca26.18497878</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>F157B4E9-6CE6-4007-835E-AFA4C4073BC8</gtr:id><gtr:title>Climate model benchmarking with glacial and mid-Holocene climates</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Climate Dynamics</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/0934c1370ca6830e6d40e3fc1a104fa9"><gtr:id>0934c1370ca6830e6d40e3fc1a104fa9</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Harrison S</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2013-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:outcomeId>5463ef87652d30.43906479</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>2F8DF383-ECD7-479C-ACD8-9C5A75D0EFD9</gtr:id><gtr:title>Ecosystem effects of CO
